According to the pilot, he flew a normal approach, but during the landing flare, the airplane 
encountered a gust of wind and bounced hard. When it did, he heard a "clunk." The airplane 
then bounced again before he made a final landing. A postaccident examination of the airplane 
revealed substantial damage to the fuselage. The pilot reported no pre-existing mechanical 
anomalies. 
The pilot's improper landing flare, which resulted in a hard landing.
